&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;M.S. Krishnan.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A 3.5 billion-year-old crater on Mars has been officially named after pioneering Indian geologist &lt;strong&gt;M.S. Krishnan&lt;/strong&gt;, along with several Kerala-based names approved by the IAU for nearby smaller landforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The IAU has named a major Martian crater after &lt;strong&gt;M.S. Krishnan&lt;/strong&gt;, recognising his foundational contributions to geological and planetary sciences.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;IAU rules allow large craters on Mars to be named after &lt;strong&gt;deceased scientists&lt;/strong&gt; who have significantly advanced planetary research.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The naming reflects international acknowledgement of India&amp;rsquo;s scientific heritage and Krishnan&amp;rsquo;s importance in Earth and planetary geology.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This is part of IAU&amp;rsquo;s systematic planetary naming process, in place since &lt;strong&gt;1919&lt;/strong&gt;, to ensure scientific consistency across planetary bodies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kerala Names Accepted by IAU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Smaller craters and a vallis near the Krishnan crater have been named &lt;strong&gt;Valiamala, Thumba, Bekal, Varkala&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Periyar&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These reflect India&amp;rsquo;s cultural and historical significance on Martian maps.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IAU Planetary Naming Rules&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Large craters: named after &lt;strong&gt;deceased scientists&lt;/strong&gt; who made major contributions to planetary science.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Small craters: named after &lt;strong&gt;towns/villages&lt;/strong&gt; with populations under 1,00,000, and names must be easy to pronounce and culturally relevant.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Planetary nomenclature provides an official registry of names for &lt;strong&gt;planets, moons and ring systems&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About M.S. Krishnan&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A pioneering Indian geologist noted for shaping modern geological research in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;His contributions laid early foundations for structural geology and Earth sciences.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Importance of Planetary Nomenclature&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ensures uniform naming standards across global scientific communities.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Helps map Martian terrain for research, exploration and mission planning.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Strengthens India&amp;rsquo;s representation in international planetary science.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lab-grown diamond sector.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mr Bakul Limbasiya, founder of Bhathwari Technologies, has been honoured with the APO National Award for his pioneering contributions to the lab-grown diamond sector.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The APO National Award recognises outstanding contributions to productivity excellence, innovation and leadership in India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bakul Limbasiya is a pioneer of the lab-grown diamond industry in India and produced the country&amp;rsquo;s first lab-grown diamond in 2004.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The award marks a milestone for India&amp;rsquo;s lab-grown diamond ecosystem, highlighting its growing strategic and economic importance.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lab-Grown Diamond Sector&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Technology-driven and sustainability-focused industry&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Supports export-led growth and employment generation&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aligned with India&amp;rsquo;s Atmanirbhar Bharat vision&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;APO National Award&lt;/strong&gt; is instituted by the Asian Productivity Organisation and administered in India by the National Productivity Council.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lab-grown diamonds&lt;/strong&gt; are manufactured using advanced technologies such as CVD and HPHT, offering a sustainable alternative to mined diamonds.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Productivity excellence&lt;/strong&gt; refers to efficient use of resources to enhance competitiveness and value creation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bhathwari Technologies Pvt. Ltd.&lt;/strong&gt; is a Surat-based company known for CVD diamond reactors and advanced lab-grown diamond technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Women&amp;rsquo;s Kabaddi World Cup.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India women&amp;rsquo;s team won their second successive Women&amp;rsquo;s Kabaddi World Cup title by defeating Chinese Taipei 35&amp;ndash;28 in Dhaka.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Women&amp;rsquo;s Kabaddi World Cup is the premier international championship for women&amp;rsquo;s kabaddi teams.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India has traditionally dominated the event, consistently performing as the world&amp;rsquo;s strongest kabaddi side.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The 2025 edition saw India remain unbeaten through knockouts, defeating Iran 33&amp;ndash;21 in the semi-final.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The final was held in Dhaka, where India overcame Chinese Taipei 35&amp;ndash;28 to lift the trophy.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chinese Taipei&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Reached the final after defeating Bangladesh 25&amp;ndash;18 in the semi-final.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Had an unbeaten run in the group stage.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Iran&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Faced India in the semi-final but lost 33&amp;ndash;21.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;One of the strongest kabaddi teams in Asia.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bangladesh&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Hosted the Women&amp;rsquo;s Kabaddi World Cup.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Reached the semi-final but lost to Chinese Taipei.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kabaddi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A contact team sport originating in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Played between two teams of seven players.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Objective: Raid into opponent territory, tag defenders, and return without being tackled.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shahrukhz by Danube.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

