&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shahrukhz by Danube&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Named after Shah Rukh Khan, this tower marks a unique intersection of celebrity and real estate branding.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Located on Sheikh Zayed Road, it offers luxury office spaces designed to attract global investors and the Indian diaspora in the Gulf region.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Danube Properties&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Developer of Shahrukhz by Danube, a key player in the Dubai real estate market.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Leveraging Shah Rukh Khan&amp;rsquo;s celebrity status enhances the project&amp;rsquo;s appeal, particularly among Indian investors.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Celebrity Branding in Real Estate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This tower is an example of how celebrity branding goes beyond endorsements to influence real estate developments, giving properties a unique identity.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It caters to investors seeking a branded address with potential value appreciation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NewSpace India Limited (NSIL).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NewSpace India Limited (NSIL) and Bengaluru-based startup GalaxEye Space have signed a Reseller Agreement for high-resolution satellite imagery.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;Under this strategic partnership, NSIL will market and distribute GalaxEye&amp;#39;s entire product portfolio, including its flagship &amp;quot;SyncFused OptoSAR&amp;quot; data, to global and domestic customers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;This marks the first time NSIL, a government-owned enterprise, has partnered with a domestic private player to act as a reseller for their satellite-generated data.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;The partnership will utilize GalaxEye&amp;rsquo;s upcoming 10-satellite constellation, starting with the launch of &amp;quot;Drishti,&amp;quot; which is slated for early 2026.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;NewSpace India Limited (NSIL)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Established - March 2019&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Headquarters - Bengaluru, Karnataka&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Role - Commercial arm of ISRO responsible for commercializing space products and launch services.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;GalaxEye Space&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Founded - 2021 (Spun off from IIT-Madras)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Technology - World&amp;rsquo;s first multi-sensor imaging satellite (OptoSAR) that combines optical and Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) data.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;CEO - Suyash Singh&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;SyncFused OptoSAR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Significance - Enables continuous high-resolution imagery during day or night and even through heavy cloud cover.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Applications - Agriculture, disaster management, infrastructure monitoring, and defense surveillance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Antrix Corporation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Description - The first commercial arm of ISRO (established in 1992) primarily focusing on international satellite launches and marketing ISRO&amp;rsquo;s products globally before NSIL&amp;rsquo;s expanded mandate.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;IN-SPACe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Role - Indian National Space Promotion and Authorisation Centre; acts as a single-window autonomous agency to promote and authorize private sector space activities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
